      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for raising this.\n\nI’ve documented how to maintain these files in a couple of places:\n\nThe commit message explains how to update:\n* MODULE.bazel.lock\n* high-availability_plugin_deps.lock.json\n\nThe plugin documentation (`src/main/resources/Documentation/build.md`) describes:\n\n* how the allowlist works\n* how to refresh it when dependencies change\n\nIn addition, the allowlist and overlap checks are enforced via Bazel tests and run in CI, so any drift is detected automatically:\n\n```\n  $ bazel test plugins/high-availability/...\n  [...]\n  //plugins/high-availability:check_high-availability_third_party_runtime_jars (cached) PASSED in 0.1s\n  //plugins/high-availability:high-availability_no_overlap_with_gerrit (cached) PASSED in 1.0s\n```\n\nHappy to improve or centralize the documentation further if you think something is still unclear.",
